A recent study sponsored by various organizations highlights the rising temperatures in the western United States, exacerbating water scarcity issues.
Global warming is projected to worsen droughts and reduce water flows in the Colorado River, impacting agriculture and urban water needs.
As the region faces chronic drought, water reallocation from farms to urban areas becomes inevitable.
Efforts are being made to restore the Colorado River delta, with proposals for bi-national water markets and conservation measures.
The looming water shortage crisis necessitates a balance between growth and sustainable water management to ensure a stable future.
